        "asset": "/systems/morphous-lavender/motif.png",
        "prompt": "Use case: photorealistic-natural\nAsset type: Morphous transparent motif chroma-key source\nPrimary request: Create only isolated lavender sprigs for a design-system motif cutout, no environment, no props, no text.\nSubject: A small natural bundle of lavender sprigs that clearly reads as real lavender: many recognizable narrow upright purple flower spikes made of tiny buds, slender sage-green stems, narrow sage leaves, and only tiny dry-straw warmth on a few woody stem tips. Not generic purple flowers, not broad petals, not lilacs.\nComposition/framing: centered complete cutout with generous padding on all sides; show full stems and flower tips without cropping; airy botanical silhouette.\nLighting/mood: clean even studio light preserving lavender-purple buds, sage-green stems/leaves, and subtle dry-straw stem warmth.\nChroma-key workflow: generate on a perfectly flat solid #ff00ff background, copy the exact generated source to .source/motif-chroma.png, then remove the key with remove_chroma_key.py using auto-key border, soft matte, and despill. The final motif.png is RGBA transparent with transparent corners.\nConstraints: no text, no watermark, no ribbon, no vase, no field background, no bouquet wrap, no broad flower petals, no extra flowers, no shadow."
