        "id": "dark-design-system",
        "label": "Dark-mode design-system board",
        "asset": "/systems/morphous-lavender/design-system-dark.png",
        "prompt": "Use case: ui-mockup\nAsset type: Morphous dark-mode design-system board\nPrimary request: Generate one separate high-resolution 16:9 dark-mode design-system board for the same Morphous theme named \"Lavender\". It must feel like the light Lavender design-system board translated to dark mode, not a new theme.\nReference use: Use the lavender sprig motif and the light Lavender board as references. Preserve motif-derived palette roles, calm scheduling component language, component coverage, spacing, typography, sage stem dividers, dry-straw accents, and lavender sprig texture.\nRequired visible sections: header \"Lavender Dark Mode\" and \"Calm scheduling system\"; Palette; Typography; Japanese Typography; Buttons; Inputs; Select; Textarea; Checkbox; Radio; Switch; Tabs; Badges; Alerts; Cards; Navigation; Sidebar; Command/Search; Tables; Charts; Empty State; Error State; Loading State; Spacing; Radius; Shadow; Texture/Pattern; Calendar App Preview.\nDark palette: deep violet and lavender-charcoal surfaces, lavender purple highlights, pale lavender text, sage green accents, dry straw warning/accent, field cream only as small text/highlight, soft grey borders, lavender ink depths. Keep colors faithful to lavender, not neon purple.\nTypography guidance: readable English and Japanese examples, with labels such as Geist, Noto Sans JP, Heading, Body, Label, Numeric, Calendar time.\nComponents: shadcn/tweakcn style, 8px card radius, dark cards and popovers, lavender primary buttons, sage secondary/support, dry straw warning/accent, visible focus rings, readable form labels, tabs, badges, alerts, command palette, table rows, charts, loading skeletons.\nCalendar app preview: dark scheduling dashboard with mini month calendar, agenda list, resource lanes, event chips, command search, sidebar navigation, charts, and table rows.\nTexture guidance: subtle lavender sprig line pattern and linen grain in dark surfaces; sage stem dividers; not decorative blobs.\nText: short readable UI labels only; include English and Japanese typography samples. Ensure \"Lavender\", \"Dark Mode\", \"Calm scheduling\", \"Typography\", \"日本語\", \"Palette\", \"Calendar\", \"Buttons\", and \"Tokens\" are legible.\nConstraints: no neon colors, no generic purple gradients, no flat pure-black-only background, no unrelated saturated colors, no illegible text, no watermark, no random brand names, no misspelling of Lavender, no light-mode board in this image."
