        "label": "Dark-mode design-system board",
        "asset": "/systems/morphous-magnolia/design-system-dark.png",
        "prompt": "Use case: ui-mockup\nAsset type: Morphous Magnolia dark-mode design-system board\nPrimary request: Generate one comprehensive dark-mode design-system board for the Morphous theme named \"Morphous Magnolia\". It must feel like the visible light-mode board translated to dark mode, not a new theme, and it must remain derived from the visible southern magnolia blossom cutout.\nCanvas: wide 16:9 high-resolution board, clean professional UI design-system presentation.\nRequired visible sections: Morphous Magnolia, Magnolia Blossom, Dark Mode, Palette, Typography, Components, Navigation, Dashboard, Forms, Table, Command/Search, Status, Texture, Radius, Spacing, Shadow, Tokens.\nReference use: Preserve the magnolia system language: branch-ink dark backgrounds, cream-petal text, magnolia-leaf controls, blush shadow highlights, warm brown borders, glossy leaf success states, layered petal cards, subtle wax-petal texture, 8px shadcn/tweakcn grid. Must read as magnolia, not water lily, lotus, dahlia, or generic luxury beige.\nTypography: English product UI examples with Japanese typography guidance; labels such as Geist, Noto Sans JP, Display, Body, Label, Numbers, 日本語 UI. Keep text short and legible.\nUI coverage: buttons, inputs, select, textarea, checkbox, radio, switch, tabs, badges, alerts, cards, table rows, search command palette, gallery navigation, portfolio dashboard metric cards, image list table, forms, empty/loading/error states, spacing, radius, border, shadow, texture samples, simple icons.\nVisual details: branch-ink and sepal-umber surfaces, cream-petal foreground, magnolia-leaf active states, blush chart highlights, warm brown dividers, subtle wax-petal overlays, restrained contrast, crisp cards and controls.\nConstraints: no lily pad, no lotus pod, no dahlia rosette, no neon colors, no generic purple/blue gradients, no pure-black-only flat background, no illegible tiny paragraphs, no watermark, no random brand names, no misspelling of \"Morphous Magnolia\"."
